The paper deals with the problem of searching for semantic associations in a large entity-relation graph, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a method for query relaxation, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a best-first search algorithm, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS) and search algorithms (cs.SI).
